<!-- Fund Accounting Help --><div class="help-section"><nav class="help-breadcrumb"><a href="/help">Help</a> / <span>Fund Accounting</span></nav><h1><i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i> Fund Accounting Explained</h1><p class="help-intro">Understanding nonprofit fund accounting principles.</p><div class="help-block"><h2>What is Fund Accounting?</h2><p>Fund accounting is a system of accounting used by nonprofits and governments that emphasizes accountability rather than profitability. Money is separated into "funds" based on restrictions on its use.</p></div><div class="help-block"><h2>Types of Net Assets</h2><table class="help-table"><tr><td><strong>Without Donor Restrictions</strong></td><td>Can be used for any purpose (formerly "Unrestricted")</td></tr><tr><td><strong>With Donor Restrictions</strong></td><td>Must be used as donor specified (formerly "Temporarily Restricted" and "Permanently Restricted")</td></tr></table></div><div class="help-block"><h2>Why It Matters</h2><ul><li><strong>Accountability</strong> - Donors trust you'll use their gift as intended</li><li><strong>Compliance</strong> - IRS and state regulators require proper fund tracking</li><li><strong>Transparency</strong> - Board and stakeholders can see how money is used</li><li><strong>Grant Management</strong> - Grantors require strict fund segregation</li></ul></div><div class="help-block"><h2>How This App Implements Fund Accounting</h2><ol><li><strong>Accounts (Funds)</strong> - Create separate accounts for each fund</li><li><strong>Account Type</strong> - Mark as Restricted/Unrestricted/Temporary</li><li><strong>Transactions</strong> - Link each transaction to appropriate fund</li><li><strong>Reports</strong> - Generate reports by fund for accountability</li></ol></div><div class="help-example"><h4>Example: Restricted Building Fund</h4><p>A donor gives $10,000 specifically for building improvements:</p><ol><li>Create account: "Building Fund" (Restricted)</li><li>Record donation: Link to Building Fund, type = Restricted</li><li>When spending: Expense from Building Fund only for building costs</li><li>Report: Show Building Fund separately in financial statements</li></ol></div></div>
